            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">4. You are asked to interpret an arterial blood gas of a 76-year-old patient who was admitted to accident and emergency with an acute onset of breathlessness and low oxygen saturations. The test was taken on room air and read as follows: pH 7.37, PO2 7.8, PCO2 4.1, HCO3 24, SO2 89 per cent. Choose the most likely clinical interpretation from these arterial blood gas results:</p>"
