            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">21. Asthma<br />\nA 25-year-old woman is admitted to accident and emergency with a severe<br />\nexacerbation of asthma. On examination, her respiratory rate is 30, oxygen<br />\nsaturations are 95 per cent on 15 L O2 and temperature is 37.2°C. As you feel the<br />\nperipheral pulse, the volume falls as the patient inspires. Which of the following<br />\nexplains this clinical sign?</p>"
